nk" rel="noopener noreferrer">remove them manually<span class="screen-reader-text"> (opens in new tab)</span></a>.','No rules currently set.'=>'No rules currently set.','Description'=>'Description','Category'=>'Category','Ignored IPs must be separated by commas or placed on separate lines. These addresses will be ignored from any alerts about increased attacks and can be used to ignore things like standalone website security scanners.'=>'Ignored IPs must be separated by commas or placed on separate lines. These addresses will be ignored from any alerts about increased attacks and can be used to ignore things like standalone website security scanners.','Separate multiple URLs with commas or place them on separate lines. Asterisks are wildcards, but use with care. If you see an attacker repeatedly probing your site for a known vulnerability you can use this to immediately block them. All URLs must start with a "/" without quotes and must be relative. e.g. /badURLone/, /bannedPage.html, /dont-access/this/URL/, /starts/with-*'=>'Separate multiple URLs with commas or place them on separate lines. Asterisks are wildcards, but use with care. If you see an attacker repeatedly probing your site for a known vulnerability you can use this to immediately block them. All URLs must start with a "/" without quotes and must be relative. e.g. /badURLone/, /bannedPage.html, /dont-access/this/URL/, /starts/with-*','You are currently running the WAF from another WordPress installation. This option can be changed once you configure the firewall to run correctly on this site.'=>'You are currently running the WAF from another WordPress installation. This option can be changed once you configure the firewall to run correctly on this site.','Advanced Firewall Options'=>'Advanced Firewall Options','No allowlisted URLs currently set.'=>'No allowlisted URLs currently set.','Created'=>'Created','Select/deselect all'=>'Select/deselect all','Monitor background requests from an administrator\'s web browser for false positives'=>'Monitor background requests from an administrator\'s web browser for false positives','Admin Panel'=>'Admin Panel','Front-end Website'=>'Front-end Website','You are currently running the Wordfence Web Application Firewall from another WordPress installation. Please <a href="%s">click here</a> to configure the Firewall to run correctly on this site.'=>'You are currently running the Wordfence Web Application Firewall from another WordPress installation. Please <a href="%s">click here</a> to configure the Firewall to run correctly on this site.','The required file has been created. You\'ll need to insert the following code into your <code>php.ini</code> to finish installation:'=>'The required file has been created. You\'ll need to insert the following code into your <code>php.ini</code> to finish installation:','Premium Protection Enabled'=>'Premium Protection Enabled','When you first install the Wordfence Web Application Firewall, it will be in learning mode. This allows Wordfence to learn about your site so that we can understand how to protect it and how to allow normal visitors through the firewall. We recommend you let Wordfence learn for a week before you enable the firewall.'=>'When you first install the Wordfence Web Application Firewall, it will be in learning mode. This allows Wordfence to learn about your site so that we can understand how to protect it and how to allow normal visitors through the firewall. We recommend you let Wordfence learn for a week before you enable the firewall.','Learning Mode Until'=>'Learning Mode Until','Learning Mode Enabled'=>'Learning Mode Enabled','The changes have not yet taken effect. If you are using LiteSpeed or IIS as your web server or CGI/FastCGI interface, you may need to wait a few minutes for the changes to take effect since the configuration files are sometimes cached. You also may need to select a different server configuration in order to complete this step, but wait for a few minutes before trying. You can try refreshing this page.'=>'The changes have not yet taken effect. If you are using LiteSpeed or IIS as your web server or CGI/FastCGI interface, you may need to wait a few minutes for the changes to take effect since the configuration files are sometimes cached. You also may need to select a different server configuration in order to complete this step, but wait for a few minutes before trying. You can try refreshing this page.','Wordfence Firewall Activated'=>'Wordfence Firewall Activated','Enable Firewall'=>'Enable Firewall','Wordfence Firewall Deactivated'=>'Wordfence Firewall Deactivated','Wordfence Firewall & Premium Enabled'=>'Wordfence Firewall & Premium Enabled','These URL patterns will be excluded from the throttling rules used to limit crawlers.'=>'These URL patterns will be excluded from the throttling rules used to limit crawlers.','block it'=>'block it','throttle it'=>'throttle it','%d per minute'=>'%d per minute','Treat Google like any other Crawler'=>'Treat Google like any other Crawler','Anyone claiming to be Google will not be rate-limited'=>'Anyone claiming to be Google will not be rate-limited','Verified Google crawlers will not be rate-limited'=>'Verified Google crawlers will not be rate-limited','NOTE: This checkbox enables ALL blocking/throttling functions including IP, country and advanced blocking, and the "Rate Limiting Rules" below.'=>'NOTE: This checkbox enables ALL blocking/throttling functions including IP, country and advanced blocking, and the "Rate Limiting Rules" below.','Manually Refresh Rules'=>'Manually Refresh Rules','You are currently running the WAF from another WordPress installation. These rules can be disabled or enabled once you configure the firewall to run correctly on this site.'=>'You are currently running the WAF from another WordPress installation. These rules can be disabled or enabled once you configure the firewall to run correctly on this site.','Rules'=>'Rules','Filter Value'=>'Filter Value','IP'=>'IP','User'=>'User','Source'=>'Source','Param'=>'Param','Disable'=>'Disable','Delete'=>'Delete','Allowlisted via Firewall Options page'=>'Allowlisted via Firewall Options page','An allowlist entry for this URL and parameter already exists.'=>'An allowlist entry for this URL and parameter already exists.','Add'=>'Add','Param Name'=>'Param Name','Query String'=>'Query String','Header'=>'Header','File Name'=>'File Name','POST Body'=>'POST Body','URL'=>'URL','The URL/parameters in this table will not be tested by the firewall. They are typically added while the firewall is in Learning Mode or by an admin who identifies a particular action/request is a false positive.'=>'The URL/parameters in this table will not be tested by the firewall. They are typically added while the firewall is in Learning Mode or by an admin who identifies a particular action/request is a false positive.','Add Allowlisted URL/Param'=>'Add Allowlisted URL/Param','Display Live Traffic menu option'=>'Display Live Traffic menu option','Maximum days to keep Live Traffic data (1-30 days)'=>'Maximum days to keep Live Traffic data (1-30 days)','Traffic logging mode'=>'Traffic logging mode','These options let you choose which traffic to log and to ignore certain types of visitors, based on their level of access, usernames, IP address, or browser type. If you run a high-traffic website where it is not feasible to see your visitors in real-time, simply change the <strong>Traffic logging mode</strong> to "Security Only."'=>'These options let you choose which traffic to log and to ignore certain types of visitors, based on their level of access, usernames, IP address, or browser type. If you run a high-traffic website where it is not feasible to see your visitors in real-time, simply change the <strong>Traffic logging mode</strong> to "Security Only."','Live Traffic Options'=>'Live Traffic Options','Enter a reason'=>'Enter a reason','e.g., *badwebsite.example.com*'=>'e.g., *badwebsite.example.com*','e.g., *badRobot*, *MSIE*, or *browserSuffix'=>'e.g., *badRobot*, *MSIE*, or *browserSuffix','e.g., *.amazonaws.com or *.linode.com'=>'e.g., *.amazonaws.com or *.linode.com','e.g., 192.168.200.200 - 192.168.200.220 or 192.168.200.0/24'=>'e.g., 192.168.200.200 - 192.168.200.220 or 192.168.200.0/24','Enter an IP address'=>'Enter an IP address','Login Form'=>'Login Form','Enter a duration (default is forever)'=>'Enter a duration (default is forever)','Block Duration'=>'Block Duration','Country Blocking'=>'Country Blocking','Country'=>'Country','Put Geographic Protection In Place With Country Blocking'=>'Put Geographic Protection In Place With Country Blocking','Enter a full URL (e.g., http://example.com/blocked/)'=>'Enter a full URL (e.g., http://example.com/blocked/)','URL to redirect blocked users to'=>'URL to redirect blocked users to','What to do when we block someone'=>'What to do when we block someone','Wordfence country blocking is designed to stop an attack, prevent content theft, or end malicious activity that originates from a geographic region in less than 1/300,000th of a second. Blocking countries who are regularly creating failed logins, a large number of page not found errors, and are clearly engaged in malicious activity is an effective way to protect your site during an attack.'=>'Wordfence country blocking is designed to stop an attack, prevent content theft, or end malicious activity that originates from a geographic region in less than 1/300,000th of a second. Blocking countries who are regularly creating failed logins, a large number of page not found errors, and are clearly engaged in malicious activity is an effective way to protect your site during an attack.','Advanced Country Blocking Options'=>'Advanced Country Blocking Options','Are you sure you want to stop blocking the %d selected IPs, ranges, and countries?'=>'Are you sure you want to stop blocking the %d selected IPs, ranges, and countries?','Are you sure you want to stop blocking the selected IP, range, or country?'=>'Are you sure you want to stop blocking the selected IP, range, or country?','Unblocking'=>'Unblocking','Change Filter'=>'Change Filter','Clear Filter'=>'Clear Filter','No blocks match the current filter.'=>'No blocks match the current filter.','No blocks are currently active.'=>'No blocks are currently active.','Last Attempt'=>'Last Attempt','Block Count'=>'Block Count','Expiration'=>'Expiration','Reason'=>'Reason','Rule Added'=>'Rule Added','Detail'=>'Detail','Block Type'=>'Block Type','Make Permanent'=>'Make Permanent','Unblock'=>'Unblock','Filter'=>'Filter','Filter by Type, Detail, or Reason'=>'Filter by Type, Detail, or Reason','Save'=>'Save','Back'=>'Back','Unblock All'=>'Unblock All','Block All'=>'Block All','Select Countries to Block from List'=>'Select Countries to Block from List','then set a cookie that will bypass country blocking in the future in case that user hits the site from a blocked country.'=>'then set a cookie that will bypass country blocking in the future in case that user hits the site from a blocked country.','/set-country-bypass/'=>'/set-country-bypass/','If user who is allowed to access the site views the relative URL'=>'If user who is allowed to access the site views the relative URL','Bypass Cookie'=>'Bypass Cookie','Manage global blocking options.'=>'Manage global blocking options.','and set a cookie that will bypass all country blocking.'=>'and set a cookie that will bypass all country blocking.','/page-name/'=>'/page-name/','then redirect that user to'=>'then redirect that user to','/bypassurl/'=>'/bypassurl/','If user hits the relative URL'=>'If user hits the relative URL','Bypass Redirect'=>'Bypass Redirect','New Login Page Captcha Feature'=>'New Login Page Captcha Feature','Two-factor authentication now has its own IP allowlist. If necessary, you can allow specific IP addresses or ranges to skip 2FA when logging in.'=>'Two-factor authentication now has its own IP allowlist. If necessary, you can allow specific IP addresses or ranges to skip 2FA when logging in.','Individual Allowlisting'=>'Individual Allowlisting','We are excited to announce the release of a completely rebuilt two-factor authentication (2FA) feature within Wordfence. 2FA is an important layer of security that protects you from password guessing and credential stuffing attacks. Previously a Premium-only feature, it is now available for sites running the free version of Wordfence. You are now able to enable 2FA for any role, we’ve added a number of important security features, and we’ve significantly improved the admin interface.'=>'We are excited to announce the release of a completely rebuilt two-factor authentication (2FA) feature within Wordfence. 2FA is an important layer of security that protects you from password guessing and credential stuffing attacks. Previously a Premium-only feature, it is now available for sites running the free version of Wordfence. You are now able to enable 2FA for any role, we’ve added a number of important security features, and we’ve significantly improved the admin interface.','Introducing the New Wordfence 2FA'=>'Introducing the New Wordfence 2FA','How do I get to 100%?'=>'How do I get to 100%?','How does Wordfence determine this?'=>'How does Wordfence determine this?','Please confirm the unsubscribe request for %s.'=>'Please confirm the unsubscribe request for %s.','Please enter an email address to unsubscribe from alerts. If this email address exists on the alert email list, it will receive a confirmation link to unsubscribe.'=>'Please enter an email address to unsubscribe from alerts. If this email address exists on the alert email list, it will receive a confirmation link to unsubscribe.','If the email address provided was on the alert email list, it has been sent an unsubscribe link.'=>'If the email address provided was on the alert email list, it has been sent an unsubscribe link.','The email address provided has been unsubscribed from future alert emails.'=>'The email address provided has been unsubscribed from future alert emails.','Confirm Unsubscribe'=>'Confirm Unsubscribe','Unsubscribe Successful'=>'Unsubscribe Successful','Unsubscription Confirmation Sent'=>'Unsubscription Confirmation Sent','Unsubscribe from Security Alerts'=>'Unsubscribe from Security Alerts','Your computer\'s time: '=>'Your computer\'s time: ','Generated by Wordfence at '=>'Generated by Wordfence at ','Please enter the license to install.'=>'Please enter the license to install.','The Wordfence license could not be installed.'=>'The Wordfence license could not be installed.','Return to the <a href="%s">Wordfence Admin Page</a>'=>'Return to the <a href="%s">Wordfence Admin Page</a>','The Wordfence license provided has been installed.'=>'The Wordfence license provided has been installed.','Install Wordfence License'=>'Install Wordfence License','Wordfence License Installation Failed'=>'Wordfence License Installation Failed','Wordfence License Installation Successful'=>'Wordfence License Installation Successful','User defined scan pattern'=>'User defined scan pattern','Enable scan option to check if your website is on a domain blocklist.'=>'Enable scan option to check if your website is on a domain blocklist.','Enable scan option to check if your website IP is generating spam.'=>'Enable scan option to check if your website IP is generating spam.','Enable scan option to check if this website is being "Spamvertised".'=>'Enable scan option to check if this website is being "Spamvertised".','Enable Premium Reputation Checks.'=>'Enable Premium Reputation Checks.','Standard detection capability'=>'Standard detection capability','Custom scan options selected'=>'Custom scan options selected','Standard detection capability, chance of false positives'=>'Standard detection capability, chance of false positives','Standard'=>'Standard','Custom'=>'Custom','High Sensitivity'=>'High Sensitivity','Limited'=>'Limited','Quick'=>'Quick','No block parameters provided.'=>'No block parameters provided.','Invalid hostname.'=>'Invalid hostname.','Invalid IP range.'=>'Invalid IP range.','Ranges mixing IPv4 and IPv6 addresses are not supported.'=>'Ranges mixing IPv4 and IPv6 addresses are not supported.','An invalid country was selected.'=>'An invalid country was selected.','No countries selected.'=>'No countries selected.','Nothing selected to block.'=>'Nothing selected to block.','Invalid IP address.'=>'Invalid IP address.','A block reason must be provided.'=>'A block reason must be provided.','Invalid block duration.'=>'Invalid block duration.','Invalid block type.'=>'Invalid block type.','Advanced Block'=>'Advanced Block','Country Block'=>'Country Block','Lockout'=>'Lockout','IP Throttled'=>'IP Throttled','IP Block'=>'IP Block','Support'=>'Support','This IP address is in a range of addresses that Wordfence does not block. The IP range may be internal or belong to a service that is always allowed. Allowlisting of external services can be disabled. <a href="%s" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Learn More<span class="screen-reader-text"> (opens in new tab)</span></a>'=>'This IP address is in a range of addresses that Wordfence does not block. The IP range may be internal or belong to a service that is always allowed. Allowlisting of external services can be disabled. <a href="%s" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Learn More<span class="screen-reader-text"> (opens in new tab)</span></a>','Dashboard'=>'Dashboard','Enable Brute Force Protection.'=>'Enable Brute Force Protection.','Disable Author Scanning.'=>'Disable Author Scanning.','Enable Block Admin Registration.'=>'Enable Block Admin Registration.','Enable Mask Login Errors.'=>'Enable Mask Login Errors.','Enforce Strong Passwords.'=>'Enforce Strong Passwords.','Enable Real-Time Wordfence Security Network.'=>'Enable Real-Time Wordfence Security Network.','Enable Real-Time IP Blocklist.'=>'Enable Real-Time IP Blocklist.','Enable Firewall.'=>'Enable Firewall.','Repair the Wordfence Firewall configuration.'=>'Repair the Wordfence Firewall configuration.','Enable Rate Limiting and Advanced Blocking.'=>'Enable Rate Limiting and Advanced Blocking.','Enable Premium Rules.'=>'Enable Premium Rules.','Enable firewall.'=>'Enable firewall.','Basic Protection'=>'Basic Protection','Extended Protection'=>'Extended Protection','Learning Mode'=>'Learning Mode','Skip'=>'Skip','Reminder: If you lose access to your authenticator device, you can use recovery codes to log in. If you have not saved a copy of your recovery codes, we recommend downloading them now.'=>'Reminder: If you lose access to your authenticator device, you can use recovery codes to log in. If you have not saved a copy of your recovery codes, we recommend downloading them now.','An error was encountered while trying to activate two-factor authentication. Please try again.'=>'An error was encountered while trying to activate two-factor authentication. Please try again.','Error Activating 2FA'=>'Error Activating 2FA','For help on setting up an app, visit our help article.'=>'For help on setting up an app, visit our help article.','Enter the code from your authenticator app below to verify and activate two-factor authentication for this account.'=>'Enter the code from your authenticator app below to verify and activate two-factor authentication for this account.','Optional'=>'Optional','Download Recovery Codes'=>'Download Recovery Codes','2. Enter Code from Authenticator App'=>'2. Enter Code from Authenticator App','An error was encountered while trying to deactivate two-factor authentication. Please try again.'=>'An error was encountered while trying to deactivate two-factor authentication. Please try again.','Error Deactivating 2FA'=>'Error Deactivating 2FA','Are you sure you want to deactivate two-factor authentication?'=>'Are you sure you want to deactivate two-factor authentication?','Deactivate 2FA'=>'Deactivate 2FA','Deactivate'=>'Deactivate','Wordfence two-factor authentication is currently active on the account <strong>%s</strong>. You may deactivate it by clicking the button below.'=>'Wordfence two-factor authentication is currently active on the account <strong>%s</strong>. You may deactivate it by clicking the button below.','Wordfence two-factor authentication is currently active on your account. You may deactivate it by clicking the button below.'=>'Wordfence two-factor authentication is currently active on your account. You may deactivate it by clicking the button below.','Wordfence 2FA Active'=>'Wordfence 2FA Active','1. Scan Code or Enter Key'=>'1. Scan Code or Enter Key','An error was encountered while trying to generate new recovery codes. Please try again.'=>'An error was encountered while trying to generate new recovery codes. Please try again.','New Recovery Codes'=>'New Recovery Codes','Each line of %d letters and numbers is a single recovery code, with optional spaces for readability. To use a recovery code, after entering your username and password, enter the code like "1234 5678 90AB CDEF" at the 2FA prompt. If your site has a custom login prompt and does not show a 2FA prompt, you can use the single-step method by entering your password and the code together in the Password field, like "mypassword1234 5678 90AB CDEF". Your recovery codes are:'=>'Each line of %d letters and numbers is a single recovery code, with optional spaces for readability. To use a recovery code, after entering your username and password, enter the code like "1234 5678 90AB CDEF" at the 2FA prompt. If your site has a custom login prompt and does not show a 2FA prompt, you can use the single-step method by entering your password and the code together in the Password field, like "mypassword1234 5678 90AB CDEF". Your recovery codes are:','Two-Factor Authentication Recovery Codes - %1$s (%2$s)'=>'Two-Factor Authentication Recovery Codes - %1$s (%2$s)','Use one of these %1$d codes to log in if you lose access to your authenticator device. Codes are %2$d characters long plus optional spaces. Each one may be used only once.'=>'Use one of these %1$d codes to log in if you lose access to your authenticator device. Codes are %2$d characters long plus optional spaces. Each one may be used only once.','Error Generating New Codes'=>'Error Generating New Codes','Generate'=>'Generate','Are you sure you want to generate new recovery codes? Any remaining unused codes will be disabled.'=>'Are you sure you want to generate new recovery codes? Any remaining unused codes will be disabled.','Generate New Recovery Codes'=>'Generate New Recovery Codes','Generate New Codes'=>'Generate New Codes','Recovery Codes'=>'Recovery Codes','If enabled, all settings and 2FA records will be deleted on deactivation. If later reactivated, all users that previously had 2FA active will need to set it up again.'=>'If enabled, all settings and 2FA records will be deleted on deactivation. If later reactivated, all users that previously had 2FA active will need to set it up again.','Delete Login Security tables and data on deactivation'=>'Delete Login Security tables and data on deactivation','While in test mode, reCAPTCHA will score login and registration requests but not actually block them. The scores will be recorded and can be used to select a human/bot threshold value.'=>'While in test mode, reCAPTCHA will score login and registration requests but not actually block them. The scores will be recorded and can be used to select a human/bot threshold value.','Run reCAPTCHA in test mode'=>'Run reCAPTCHA in test mode','Allowlisted IPs must be placed on separate lines. You can specify ranges using the following formats: 127.0.0.1/24, 127.0.0.[1-100], or 127.0.0.1-127.0.1.100.'=>'Allowlisted IPs must be placed on separate lines. You can specify ranges using the following formats: 127.0.0.1/24, 127.0.0.[1-100], or 127.0.0.1-127.0.1.100.','Disable XML-RPC authentication'=>'Disable XML-RPC authentication','Required'=>'Required','Skipped'=>'Skipped','If enabled, XML-RPC calls that require authentication will also require a valid 2FA code to be appended to the password. You must choose the "Skipped" option if you use the WordPress app, the Jetpack plugin, or other services that require XML-RPC.'=>'If enabled, XML-RPC calls that require authentication will also require a valid 2FA code to be appended to the password. You must choose the "Skipped" option if you use the WordPress app, the Jetpack plugin, or other services that require XML-RPC.','If enabled, users with 2FA enabled may choose to be prompted for a code only once every 30 days per device.'=>'If enabled, users with 2FA enabled may choose to be prompted for a code only once every 30 days per device.','Allow remembering device for 30 days'=>'Allow remembering device for 30 days','Super Administrator'=>'Super Administrator','* User counts currently only reflect the main site on multisite installations.'=>'* User counts currently only reflect the main site on multisite installations.','Total Users'=>'Total Users','Role'=>'Role','Manage Users'=>'Manage Users','User Summary'=>'User Summary','Detected IP:'=>'Detected IP:','Corrected Time (WF):'=>'Corrected Time (WF):','Corrected Time (NTP):'=>'Corrected Time (NTP):','Browser Time:'=>'Browser Time:','Server Time:'=>'Server Time:','(you)'=>'(you)','Editing User:&nbsp;&nbsp;%1$s <span class="wfls-text-plain">%2$s</span>'=>'Editing User:&nbsp;&nbsp;%1$s <span class="wfls-text-plain">%2$s</span>','Two-Factor Authentication, or 2FA, significantly improves login security for your website. Wordfence 2FA works with a number of TOTP-based apps like Google Authenticator, FreeOTP, and Authy. For a full list of tested TOTP-based apps, <a href="%s" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">click here</a>.'=>'Two-Factor Authentication, or 2FA, significantly improves login security for your website. Wordfence 2FA works with a number of TOTP-based apps like Google Authenticator, FreeOTP, and Authy. For a full list of tested TOTP-based apps, <a href="%s" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">click here</a>.','The request was flagged as suspicious, and we need verification that you attempted to log in to allow it to proceed. This verification link <b>will be valid for 15 minutes</b> from the time it was sent. If you did not attempt this login, please change your password immediately.'=>'The request was flagged as suspicious, and we need verification that you attempted to log in to allow it to proceed. This verification link <b>will be valid for 15 minutes</b> from the time it was sent. If you did not attempt this login, please change your password immediately.','IP:'=>'IP:','Request Time:'=>'Request Time:','Count'=>'Count','reCAPTCHA Score History'=>'reCAPTCHA Score History','Requests'=>'Requests','Reset Score Statistics'=>'Reset Score Statistics','A reCAPTCHA score equal to or higher than this value will be considered human. Anything lower will be treated as a bot and require additional verification for login and registration.'=>'A reCAPTCHA score equal to or higher than this value will be considered human. Anything lower will be treated as a bot and require additional verification for login and registration.','reCAPTCHA human/bot threshold score'=>'reCAPTCHA human/bot threshold score','(definitely a human)'=>'(definitely a human)','reCAPTCHA v3 Secret'=>'reCAPTCHA v3 Secret','reCAPTCHA v3 Site Key'=>'reCAPTCHA v3 Site Key','reCAPTCHA v3 does not make users solve puzzles or click a checkbox like previous versions. The only visible part is the reCAPTCHA logo. If a visitor\'s browser fails the CAPTCHA, Wordfence will send an email to the user\'s address with a link they can click to verify that they are a user of your site. You can read further details <a href="%s" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">in our documentation</a>.'=>'reCAPTCHA v3 does not make users solve puzzles or click a checkbox like previous versions. The only visible part is the reCAPTCHA logo. If a visitor\'s browser fails the CAPTCHA, Wordfence will send an email to the user\'s address with a link they can click to verify that they are a user of your site. You can read further details <a href="%s" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">in our documentation</a>.','Enable reCAPTCHA on the login and user registration pages'=>'Enable reCAPTCHA on the login and user registration pages','These IPs (or CIDR ranges) will be ignored when determining the requesting IP via the X-Forwarded-For HTTP header. Enter one IP or CIDR range per line.'=>'These IPs (or CIDR ranges) will be ignored when determining the requesting IP via the X-Forwarded-For HTTP header. Enter one IP or CIDR range per line.','How to get IPs'=>'How to get IPs','Use the X-Real-IP HTTP header. Only use if you have a front-end proxy or spoofing may result.'=>'Use the X-Real-IP HTTP header. Only use if you have a front-end proxy or spoofing may result.','Use the X-Forwarded-For HTTP header. Only use if you have a front-end proxy or spoofing may result.'=>'Use the X-Forwarded-For HTTP header. Only use if you have a front-end proxy or spoofing may result.','Use PHP\'s built in REMOTE_ADDR and don\'t use anything else. Very secure if this is compatible with your site.'=>'Use PHP\'s built in REMOTE_ADDR and don\'t use anything else. Very secure if this is compatible with your site.','Recommended'=>'Recommended','Use the most secure method to get visitor IP addresses. Prevents spoofing and works with most sites.'=>'Use the most secure method to get visitor IP addresses. Prevents spoofing and works with most sites.','Premium Feature'=>'Premium Feature','An error was encountered while trying to send the notification. Please try again.'=>'An error was encountered while trying to send the notification. Please try again.','Notification Sent'=>'Notification Sent','Error Sending Notification'=>'Error Sending Notification','If you\'re looking for a more comprehensive solution, the <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/wor